The paper deals with the problem of compressing high-coverage sequencing data, which involves handling large amounts of DNA sequences. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) category, as well as the Information Theory (cs.IT) category, which deals with data compression. The paper also mentions disk-based solutions, which could place it in the categories of Computer Engineering (cs.CE) and Databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper achieves a high compression ratio, which could make it relevant to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) category.
